<h1>Arbuzov Reaction<br>Michaelis-Arbuzov Reaction</h1>
<p><img src="arbuzo1.gif" width="364" height="66"></p>
<p>The reaction of a trialkyl phosphite with an alkyl halide to produce an 
alkyl phosphonate. The first step involves nucleophilic attack by the 
phosphorus on the alkyl halide, followed by the halide ion dealkylation 
of the resulting trialkoxyphosphonium salt.</p>
<p>This reaction sees extensive application in the preparation of 
phosphonate esters for use in the Horner-Emmons Reaction.</p>
<hr>
